column5: Has anyone heard things about some of the island resorts? I was just at the Milwaukee show, and someone informed me that at least two of the resorts have recently sold. I don't want to say names, incase they're rumors. But, was interested in seeing if they were actually true. (This doesn't count Todd at Tamarak)
This is old news but what will happen to Hiden Island Lodge. They closed a couple years ago

Hidden island was purchased again late last summer by a couple from Ontario. At least that's what I was told. After some searching, I found some confirmation on one of the rumors I'd heard. Someone at the show told me Black Island had indeed sold. http://www.borderlandrealty.com/list...ail.php?id=133
They both are in prime fishing territory, as is Obabikon. Bill
Obabikon,Black Island camp was purchased by Ballard's Resort. Here is their link: http://www.blackisland.com/.Mark
